<item>
            <title>[LU-12924] scale precreate_batch for larger OSTs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12924</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using large capacity OST targets, we frequently increase &lt;tt&gt;obdfilter.&amp;#42;.precreate_batch&lt;/tt&gt; since this appears to improve mdtest benchmark results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently the &lt;tt&gt;obdfilter.&amp;#42;.precreate_batch&lt;/tt&gt; values scale somewhat for small capacity OST targets; from 8 (&amp;lt;=1GB OST) to 128 (larger OSTs). However max value of 128 has not changed in several years.  mdest benchmarks suggest larger capacity OST targets (e.g. 512T) would benefit from a &lt;tt&gt;precreate_batch&lt;/tt&gt; value of 256 or larger.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
